{"env":{"SHELL":"/bin/bash","TERM":"xterm-256color"},"height":30,"timestamp":1777841085,"title":"glacier vibe --help","version":2,"width":90}
[0,"o","\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\n  glacier vibe [flags]\n\n  Animated bear + tip rotation; ambient framework reference.\n\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\n  Plays an animated polar bear with the Glacier wordmark and a\n  rotating tip from the framework's documentation. Press any key to\n  exit.\n  \n  Use --ascii on terminals without UTF-8 or color support;\n  use --duration to bound the animation; use --no-tips to suppress\n  the tip footer.\n\n\u001b[1mFLAGS\u001b[0m\n  \u001b[33m    --ascii\u001b[0m           Forces the kaomoji-only fallback even on capable terminals\n  \u001b[33m    --duration \u003cint\u003e\u001b[0m  Bounds the loop. Default 0s means run until key press or SIGINT\n  \u001b[33m    --notips\u001b[0m          Suppresses the rotating tip line\n  \u001b[33m    --seed \u003cint\u003e\u001b[0m      Seeds the tip-rotation order. 0 means time-based\n\nRun \u001b[4mglacier --help\u001b[0m for global flags.\n"]
